// A `Vec` slice, written low-first (planning/slicing.md): `v[2..5]` is the
// half-open interval [2, 5) — elements {2,3,4}, width 3. A two-endpoint Vec
// slice resolves to the inherent `Vec` slice impl in the prelude, which reduces
// it to the offset form `v[2 ..+ 3]` and so lowers to the native part-select
// `v[2 +: 3]` in the backend.
fn s(v: Vec(8, uint(4))) -> Vec(3, uint(4)) {
    v[2..5]
}
